# ==========================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ==========================================
#
# Issue: "API_KEY not set" warning in console
# Solution: 
#   - Make sure this file is named .env.local (with the dot)
#   - File must be in restaurant-frontend folder (same level as package.json)
#   - Variable must start with REACT_APP_
#   - Restart frontend after creating file
#
# Issue: "CORS error" in browser console
# Solution:
#   - Check REACT_APP_API_URL is correct (http://localhost:3001)
#   - Check backend .env has FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3000
#   - Make sure backend is running
#   - Restart backend after changing its .env
#
# Issue: "401 Unauthorized" on all API calls
# Solution:
#   - API keys don't match!
#   - Backend .env: API_KEY=abc123
#   - Frontend .env.local: REACT_APP_API_KEY=abc123
#   - They MUST be IDENTICAL
#   - Keys are case-sensitive
#
# Issue: "Network error" message
# Solution:
#   - Backend is not running
#   - Start backend: cd restaurant-backend && npm run start:dev
#   - Verify backend health: curl http://localhost:3001/health
#
# Issue: Configuration not updating
# Solution:
#   - Stop frontend: Ctrl+C
#   - Delete .env.local
#   - Create new .env.local with correct values
#   - Start frontend: npm start
#   - Hard refresh browser: Cmd+Shift+R (Mac) or Ctrl+Shift+R (Windows)
#
# Issue: "localhost" showing in production
# Solution:
#   - This file is for local development only
#   - In production (Vercel), set environment variables in dashboard:
#     1. Go to Vercel dashboard
#     2. Your project ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Environment Variables
#     3. Add REACT_APP_API_URL = https://your-backend.onrender.com
#     4. Add REACT_APP_API_KEY = your-production-key
#     5. Redeploy frontend
# ==========================================


