# ==========================================
# REACT ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES NOTES
# ==========================================
#
# React has specific rules for environment variables:
#
# 1. Must start with REACT_APP_
#    ‚úÖ REACT_APP_API_URL (works)
#    ‚ùå API_URL (ignored by React)
#
# 2. Set at build time (not runtime)
#    - Values are embedded in bundle during build
#    - Changing .env requires rebuild
#    - npm start rebuilds automatically
#    - Production: must rebuild and redeploy
#
# 3. File priority (highest to lowest):
#    - .env.local (local overrides, not committed)
#    - .env.development (dev defaults, can commit)
#    - .env.production (prod defaults, can commit)
#    - .env (base defaults, can commit)
#
# 4. Available in code via process.env
#    const url = process.env.REACT_APP_API_URL;
#
# 5. Not available in HTML files
#    Use %REACT_APP_VAR_NAME% syntax instead
#
# Read more: https://create-react-app.dev/docs/adding-custom-environment-variables
# ==========================================


